527
00:22:57,288 --> 00:22:58,455
Hi, Daddy.

528
00:22:58,539 --> 00:23:00,874
Wow, you're answering
the phone now, huh, buddy?

529
00:23:00,958 --> 00:23:03,501
-Big man now.
-ETHAN: <i>Yeah.</i>

530
00:23:03,585 --> 00:23:05,045
Hey, put your mommy on, okay?

531
00:23:05,129 --> 00:23:06,546
Okay.

532
00:23:06,630 --> 00:23:08,590
ETHAN: Phone!

533
00:23:10,551 --> 00:23:12,093
Hello?

534
00:23:12,177 --> 00:23:13,929
Who the fuck is this?

535
00:23:14,013 --> 00:23:16,014
<i>-Who the fuck is this?</i>
-This is Joel.

536
00:23:16,098 --> 00:23:17,557
-Who?
<i>-Midge's husband. Who are you?</i>

537
00:23:17,641 --> 00:23:18,808
Susie.

538
00:23:18,892 --> 00:23:21,478
-Susie who?
<i>-From the Gaslight.</i>

539
00:23:21,562 --> 00:23:22,979
What the hell are you doing there?

540
00:23:23,063 --> 00:23:25,023
<i>I don't know.
Why the hell are you calling?</i>

541
00:23:25,107 --> 00:23:27,108
-Midge is my wife.
-Not anymore.

542
00:23:27,192 --> 00:23:30,070
I asked Ethan to put his mother on…
why'd he put you on?

543
00:23:30,154 --> 00:23:31,780
I don't know, he's your idiot kid.

544
00:23:31,864 --> 00:23:33,406
You know what?

545
00:23:33,490 --> 00:23:35,367
-Is Midge there?
<i>-No.</i>

546
00:23:35,451 --> 00:23:36,785
Can you take a message?

547
00:23:36,869 --> 00:23:38,411
-No.
<i>-Will you take a message?</i>

548
00:23:38,495 --> 00:23:40,914
<i>I need her to meet me. It's important.</i>

549
00:23:40,998 --> 00:23:43,041
<i>-Hello?</i>
-Fine.

550
00:23:43,125 --> 00:23:45,502
<i>Tell Midge to meet me at 15 West 40th.</i>

551
00:23:45,586 --> 00:23:47,921
JOEL: I… I like the molding,

552
00:23:48,005 --> 00:23:49,339
but I may want to strip the paint off.

553
00:23:49,423 --> 00:23:51,424
-Is that possible?
-MAN: It's getting late.

554
00:23:51,508 --> 00:23:54,803
-Knock-knock.
-Midge, great. Come in.

555
00:23:54,887 --> 00:23:56,304
I'd like you to meet Mr. Greenberg.

556
00:23:56,388 --> 00:23:57,807
Mr. Greenberg owns the building.

557
00:23:57,891 --> 00:24:00,768
Oh, well, your parents
must be so very proud.

558
00:24:00,852 --> 00:24:03,729
Don't touch anything.
The paint's not dry.

559
00:24:03,813 --> 00:24:06,148
-Well, he's a charmer.
-He's fine.

560
00:24:06,232 --> 00:24:08,484
The most important thing
is he keeps a clean building.

561
00:24:08,568 --> 00:24:11,320
Anyhow, thank you for coming.

562
00:24:11,404 --> 00:24:13,447
-You said it was important.
-I know.

563
00:24:13,531 --> 00:24:15,866
I didn't mean to be
dramatic, but I… I've toured

564
00:24:15,950 --> 00:24:17,743
a lot of shitholes over
the past few weeks,

565
00:24:17,827 --> 00:24:19,662
so when I finally found this place,

566
00:24:19,746 --> 00:24:22,248
I had to get you down here
before someone else took it.

567
00:24:22,332 --> 00:24:24,458
What are you talking about? What is this?

568
00:24:24,542 --> 00:24:27,753
Your new apartment. [CHUCKLES]

569
00:24:27,837 --> 00:24:29,630
I really think it's the
perfect place for you.

570
00:24:29,714 --> 00:24:33,217
-For me?
-And Ethan and Esther.

571
00:24:33,301 --> 00:24:35,011
I know it's smaller than you're used to,

572
00:24:35,095 --> 00:24:38,055
but it's very clean, it's
an elevator building.

573
00:24:38,139 --> 00:24:40,599
It's a great location, halfway
between the club downtown

574
00:24:40,683 --> 00:24:42,143
and your parents' apartment.

575
00:24:42,227 --> 00:24:43,519
There's a great park a block away.

576
00:24:43,603 --> 00:24:44,770
The butcher's right around the corner,

577
00:24:44,854 --> 00:24:46,063
and it's right off three subways.

578
00:24:46,147 --> 00:24:48,858
I can manage it, and you
won't have to work anymore.

579
00:24:48,942 --> 00:24:51,402
Whoa, whoa, whoa, who
says I'm gonna stop working?

580
00:24:51,486 --> 00:24:53,904
-Well, you'll have to.
-Oh, I will?

581
00:24:53,988 --> 00:24:55,531
-Why will I have to?
-I…

582
00:24:55,615 --> 00:24:57,908
Am I suddenly unable to apply lipstick?

583
00:24:57,992 --> 00:24:59,577
-No.
-I can't point to powder?

584
00:24:59,661 --> 00:25:01,454
-You can point.
-I can't spritz a person

585
00:25:01,538 --> 00:25:03,205
with perfume?
That's where my abilities end?

586
00:25:03,289 --> 00:25:04,623
You'll have the kids.
You won't have your parents

587
00:25:04,707 --> 00:25:05,666
or Zelda around.

588
00:25:05,750 --> 00:25:06,917
I figured you'd want to quit.

589
00:25:07,001 --> 00:25:08,169
Oh, you figured. You figured?

590
00:25:08,253 --> 00:25:09,962
-What's the matter?
-I just don't like you

591
00:25:10,046 --> 00:25:11,297
telling me where I'm gonna live.

592
00:25:11,381 --> 00:25:12,381
I wasn't telling you.

593
00:25:12,465 --> 00:25:13,758
Where are you gonna live, huh?

594
00:25:13,842 --> 00:25:15,009
-Me?
-Yeah, you're still

595
00:25:15,093 --> 00:25:16,510
-at your parents', right?
-Yes.

596
00:25:16,594 --> 00:25:17,803
Well, if you can tell me
where I'm gonna live,

597
00:25:17,887 --> 00:25:18,777
then I can tell you
where you're gonna live.

598
00:25:18,861 --> 00:25:19,013
Midge.

599
00:25:19,097 --> 00:25:20,514
Turtle Bay.
You're gonna live in Turtle Bay.

600
00:25:20,598 --> 00:25:22,641
-Where the hell is Turtle Bay?
-I don't know.

601
00:25:22,725 --> 00:25:24,101
It's right off three subways. Have fun!

602
00:25:24,185 --> 00:25:25,728
-Why are you angry?
-I'm not angry.

603
00:25:25,812 --> 00:25:27,938
-It's a nice apartment.
-I had a nice apartment.

604
00:25:28,022 --> 00:25:29,857
-I know.
-And I lost it because of you.

605
00:25:29,941 --> 00:25:31,275
I know.

606
00:25:31,359 --> 00:25:33,110
And it was right off three subways, too.

607
00:25:33,194 --> 00:25:34,528
It wasn't, actually.

608
00:25:34,612 --> 00:25:36,530
How can you suddenly afford this?

609
00:25:36,614 --> 00:25:38,574
Huh? You quit your job.

610
00:25:38,658 --> 00:25:40,201
-Right?
-Uh…

611
00:25:40,285 --> 00:25:41,619
Imogene said that you quit your job,

612
00:25:41,703 --> 00:25:42,953
and now Archie's gonna get fired.

613
00:25:43,037 --> 00:25:44,163
Why is Archie gonna get fired?

614
00:25:44,247 --> 00:25:45,498
I don't know. Ask Imogene.

615
00:25:45,582 --> 00:25:47,541
She said that you walked
out and left Archie standing

616
00:25:47,625 --> 00:25:49,043
next to the chart that she made.

617
00:25:49,127 --> 00:25:50,503
-Imogene made that chart?
-Yes.

618
00:25:50,587 --> 00:25:51,630
That was a great chart.

619
00:25:51,714 --> 00:25:52,714
So you get another job?

620
00:25:52,798 --> 00:25:55,050
-Midge, I've got it covered.
-How?

621
00:25:55,134 --> 00:25:56,218
Do you like the apartment or not?

622
00:25:56,302 --> 00:25:59,638
-No.
-Fine.

623
00:25:59,722 --> 00:26:01,264
Yes, it's very nice.

624
00:26:01,348 --> 00:26:03,975
The phone niche is
particularly delightful.

625
00:26:04,059 --> 00:26:06,311
I'm sorry, it's not the apartment.

626
00:26:06,395 --> 00:26:09,106
The apartment's fine. It's just a lot…

627
00:26:09,190 --> 00:26:11,316
I can find my own place.

628
00:26:11,400 --> 00:26:13,235
Okay, find your own place.

629
00:26:13,319 --> 00:26:15,070
Just tell me what it
costs and I'll pay for it.

630
00:26:15,154 --> 00:26:16,863
With the job you don't have yet?

631
00:26:16,947 --> 00:26:18,657
Midge, give me a break, please?

632
00:26:18,741 --> 00:26:21,326
I'm just trying to do some
fucking thing right here!

633
00:26:21,410 --> 00:26:26,123
I know. I know.

634
00:26:26,207 --> 00:26:28,708
Sorry to drag you out here like this.

635
00:26:28,792 --> 00:26:33,631
It's a nice place, it's just… I get it.

636
00:26:39,762 --> 00:26:41,680
I don't want you to live in Turtle Bay.

637
00:26:41,764 --> 00:26:44,182
I don't either.

638
00:26:44,266 --> 00:26:46,435
Okay.

639
00:26:46,519 --> 00:26:48,771
Well, that's settled.

640
00:26:51,190 --> 00:26:53,525
ABE: No, no, no, no, no, I… I can do this.

641
00:26:53,609 --> 00:26:55,444
I am a learned man, I
teach at a major university.

642
00:26:55,528 --> 00:26:56,611
ROSE: Fine.

643
00:26:56,695 --> 00:26:58,780
Ah! Thursday, right there.

644
00:26:58,864 --> 00:27:00,198
That says "Thursday."

645
00:27:00,282 --> 00:27:02,909
Bravo. Ethan would be very proud of you.

646
00:27:02,993 --> 00:27:06,246
See, I hear some very
French sarcasm in that "bravo."

647
00:27:06,330 --> 00:27:08,206
<i>Pas du tout!</i> That means "not at all."

648
00:27:08,290 --> 00:27:09,916
-[CHUCKLES]
-Are you ready?

649
00:27:10,000 --> 00:27:11,209
For what?

650
00:27:11,293 --> 00:27:12,669
ROSE [SINGSONG]: Come on.

651
00:27:12,753 --> 00:27:14,337
Rose, where are you taking me?

652
00:27:14,421 --> 00:27:16,673
Rose, you're being very mysterious.

653
00:27:16,757 --> 00:27:18,592
ROSE: Am I? We're here.

654
00:27:18,676 --> 00:27:21,428
It's so exciting.

655
00:27:27,101 --> 00:27:28,894
Voilà!

656
00:27:28,978 --> 00:27:30,854
ABE: What is this?

657
00:27:30,938 --> 00:27:33,899
Jeanne, from my class,
her parents own the building.

658
00:27:33,983 --> 00:27:35,484
The tenants just moved out,

659
00:27:35,568 --> 00:27:37,194
so they haven't had the
chance to fix it up yet,

660
00:27:37,278 --> 00:27:38,737
but I just had to show
it to you immediately.

661
00:27:38,821 --> 00:27:40,363
Obviously, it needs some paint

662
00:27:40,447 --> 00:27:42,365
and some repairs here and
there, but look at the view.

663
00:27:42,449 --> 00:27:43,742
ABE: Ooh, that's some view.

664
00:27:43,826 --> 00:27:45,744
See over there? That's your café.

665
00:27:45,828 --> 00:27:47,371
-So it is.
-Five blocks away.

666
00:27:47,455 --> 00:27:49,790
-Ah.
-There are two bedrooms back here.

667
00:27:49,874 --> 00:27:51,834
A perfect little kitchen, bathroom.

668
00:27:51,918 --> 00:27:53,336
-Look at that ceiling.
-Isn't it marvelous?

669
00:27:53,420 --> 00:27:55,213
I almost don't want them to fix it up.

670
00:27:55,297 --> 00:27:57,590
It's sort of glorious in its shabbiness.

671
00:27:57,674 --> 00:28:00,593
-[LAUGHS]
-We… We could put a sofa there,

672
00:28:00,677 --> 00:28:02,386
some chairs, right over here your piano.

673
00:28:02,470 --> 00:28:03,513
-Ooh, yes.
-[SNAPS FINGERS]

674
00:28:03,597 --> 00:28:04,805
The acoustics are perfect.

675
00:28:04,889 --> 00:28:06,349
The dining room would go in here.

676
00:28:06,433 --> 00:28:09,393
We could fit eight
comfortably, ten with a leaf.

677
00:28:09,477 --> 00:28:12,605
And right over here would be
a great place for you to read.

678
00:28:12,689 --> 00:28:14,857
Oh, yes, perfect reading light.

679
00:28:14,941 --> 00:28:18,361
This wall is for bookshelves,
I think a console over here.

680
00:28:18,445 --> 00:28:20,029
A radio, record player…

681
00:28:20,113 --> 00:28:21,364
-Are they dog friendly?
-They're dog friendly.

682
00:28:21,448 --> 00:28:22,907
They have to be dog friendly.

683
00:28:22,991 --> 00:28:24,492
Plus, there's a little
park around the corner

684
00:28:24,576 --> 00:28:25,576
where we could throw her little ball.

685
00:28:25,660 --> 00:28:26,661
She loves that little ball.

686
00:28:26,745 --> 00:28:28,287
It's special, isn't it?

687
00:28:28,371 --> 00:28:31,499
-Well, it is just a ball.
-No, the apartment.

688
00:28:31,583 --> 00:28:33,834
-Oh, yes, it's magnificent.
-I know.

689
00:28:33,918 --> 00:28:35,378
I mean, I love our little place,

690
00:28:35,462 --> 00:28:37,713
but it's not very
practical for the long term.

691
00:28:37,797 --> 00:28:40,841
Though I will miss the boys,
but we'll just have to get used to

692
00:28:40,925 --> 00:28:42,260
our own bathroom again.

693
00:28:42,344 --> 00:28:44,845
And hot water, we'll have to
get used to hot water again.

694
00:28:44,929 --> 00:28:49,433
-Rose.
-[ROSE CONTINUES INDISTINCTLY]

695
00:28:49,517 --> 00:28:51,686
-Rose.
-Hmm?

696
00:28:53,855 --> 00:28:56,274
We can't buy this apartment.

697
00:28:56,358 --> 00:28:57,650
Why not?

698
00:28:57,734 --> 00:28:59,694
Because we don't live here.

699
00:28:59,778 --> 00:29:01,445
Well, we will after we buy the place.

700
00:29:01,529 --> 00:29:03,573
In Paris, we don't live in Paris.

701
00:29:03,657 --> 00:29:04,907
We have to go home.

702
00:29:04,991 --> 00:29:06,409
Paris is home.

703
00:29:06,493 --> 00:29:08,077
No, Rose, it's not.

704
00:29:08,161 --> 00:29:09,662
Why not?

705
00:29:09,746 --> 00:29:11,914
Because my classes at
Columbia start in a week.

706
00:29:11,998 --> 00:29:13,749
I'm a tenured professor.

707
00:29:13,833 --> 00:29:16,043
And if I don't go back, I'll
lose my spot at Bell Labs.

708
00:29:16,127 --> 00:29:18,629
And if I don't go back, what will I lose?

709
00:29:18,713 --> 00:29:21,549
-Well…
-Drapes will have to be made,

710
00:29:21,633 --> 00:29:23,134
but the shutters will do for now.

711
00:29:23,218 --> 00:29:25,761
Rose, stop. Our lives are in New York.

712
00:29:25,845 --> 00:29:27,179
Your friends are in New York.

713
00:29:27,263 --> 00:29:28,764
Your… Your garden club is in New York.

714
00:29:28,848 --> 00:29:31,058
I have friends here, too. So do you.

715
00:29:31,142 --> 00:29:33,185
-What friends?
-What are you talking about?

716
00:29:33,269 --> 00:29:35,896
Thierry, Rolf, Sergei.
Have you forgotten about them?

717
00:29:35,980 --> 00:29:37,773
Of course not.

718
00:29:37,857 --> 00:29:39,900
You're part of their group;
you're… you're one of them.

719
00:29:39,984 --> 00:29:43,822
I am not one of th…
I have no idea what they're talking about.

720
00:29:43,906 --> 00:29:46,450
They could be sitting there
saying, "That idiot, Abe,

721
00:29:46,534 --> 00:29:48,869
"thinks we like him.
Let's set his coat on fire,

722
00:29:48,953 --> 00:29:50,912
and see how long it takes him to notice."

723
00:29:50,996 --> 00:29:52,623
